title: SIC! SIC! SIC!
html:
SIC! SIC! SIC!

Prices [of gasoline] are hitting near-record highs, blamed by oil industry officials on an unstable foreign supply and a low inventory—or artificial manipulation of the market by oil-industry critics. [ from The Journal News (Westchester County, N.Y.) August 29, 2003. Submitted by Stephen E. Hirschberg, MD, Elmsford, New York. “Oh, those manipulative critics!”]
